{
  "texts": [
    "After running RagTag scaffold, the placed contigs had the exact same lengths as the primary contigs before running RagTag scaffold.",
    "Also, the number of gaps in each RagTag assembly corresponds to the number of placed contigs minus seven (number of chromosomes) (Supplementary Table 6).",
    "This indicates that RagTag scaffold did not introduce misassemblies or duplicated contig ends.",
    "The scaffolded assemblies were validated with dot-plots generated using Mash-Map (v3.0.6) 60 against the corresponding reference assembly.",
    "While being great resources for gene discovery and comparative analyses, reference-guided assemblies are limited in their ability to study large structural rearrangements."
  ]
}